15 Section 561. The Legislature finds and declares that the
16 distribution and sale of new motor vehicles and powersport vehicles
17 in the State of Oklahoma this state vitally affects the general
18 economy of the state and the public interest and the public welfare,
19 and that in order to promote the public interest and the public
20 welfare, and in the exercise of its police powers, it is necessary
21 to regulate and to license motor vehicle manufacturers, factories,
22 distributors, and their respective representatives, new motor
23 vehicle dealers, and powersport vehicle dealers, and to register
24 salespersons of new motor vehicles and powersport vehicles doing
